19473 silly install resolved     name: 'imurmurhash',
19473 silly install resolved     version: '0.1.4',
19473 silly install resolved     description: 'An incremental implementation of MurmurHash3',
19473 silly install resolved     homepage: 'https://github.com/jensyt/imurmurhash-js',
19473 silly install resolved     main: 'imurmurhash.js',
19473 silly install resolved     files: [
19473 silly install resolved       'imurmurhash.js',
19473 silly install resolved       'imurmurhash.min.js',
19473 silly install resolved       'package.json',
19473 silly install resolved       'README.md'
19473 silly install resolved     ],
19473 silly install resolved     repository: {
19473 silly install resolved       type: 'git',
19473 silly install resolved       url: 'git+https://github.com/jensyt/imurmurhash-js.git'
19473 silly install resolved     },
19473 silly install resolved     bugs: { url: 'https://github.com/jensyt/imurmurhash-js/issues' },
19473 silly install resolved     keywords: [ 'murmur', 'murmurhash', 'murmurhash3', 'hash', 'incremental' ],
19473 silly install resolved     author: {
19473 silly install resolved       name: 'Jens Taylor',
19473 silly install resolved       email: 'jensyt@gmail.com',
19473 silly install resolved       url: 'https://github.com/homebrewing'
19473 silly install resolved     },
19473 silly install resolved     license: 'MIT',
19473 silly install resolved     dependencies: {},
19473 silly install resolved     devDependencies: {},
19473 silly install resolved     engines: { node: '>=0.8.19' },
19473 silly install resolved     readme: 'iMurmurHash.js\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '==============\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       "An incremental implementation of the MurmurHash3 (32-bit) hashing algorithm for JavaScript based on [Gary Court's implementation](https://github.com/garycourt/murmurhash-js) with [kazuyukitanimura's modifications](https://github.com/kazuyukitanimura/murmurhash-js).\n" +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'This version works significantly faster than the non-incremental version if you need to hash many small strings into a single hash, since string concatenation (to build the single string to pass the non-incremental version) is fairly costly. In one case tested, using the incremental version was about 50% faster than concatenating 5-10 strings and then hashing.\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'Installation\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '------------\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'To use iMurmurHash in the browser, [download the latest version](https://raw.github.com/jensyt/imurmurhash-js/master/imurmurhash.min.js) and include it as a script on your site.\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '```html\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '<script type="text/javascript" src="/scripts/imurmurhash.min.js"></script>\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '<script>\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '// Your code here, access iMurmurHash using the global object MurmurHash3\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '</script>\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '```\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '---\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'To use iMurmurHash in Node.js, install the module using NPM:\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '```bash\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'npm install imurmurhash\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '```\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'Then simply include it in your scripts:\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '```javascript\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       "MurmurHash3 = require('imurmurhash');\n" +
19473 silly install resolved       '```\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'Quick Example\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '-------------\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '```javascript\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '// Create the initial hash\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       "var hashState = MurmurHash3('string');\n" +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '// Incrementally add text\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       "hashState.hash('more strings');\n" +
19473 silly install resolved       "hashState.hash('even more strings');\n" +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '// All calls can be chained if desired\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       "hashState.hash('and').hash('some').hash('more');\n" +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '// Get a result\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'hashState.result();\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '// returns 0xe4ccfe6b\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '```\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'Functions\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '---------\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '### MurmurHash3 ([string], [seed])\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'Get a hash state object, optionally initialized with the given _string_ and _seed_. _Seed_ must be a positive integer if provided. Calling this function without the `new` keyword will return a cached state object that has been reset. This is safe to use as long as the object is only used from a single thread and no other hashes are created while operating on this one. If this constraint cannot be met, you can use `new` to create a new state object. For example:\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '```javascript\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '// Use the cached object, calling the function again will return the same\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '// object (but reset, so the current state would be lost)\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'hashState = MurmurHash3();\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '...\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '// Create a new object that can be safely used however you wish. Calling the\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '// function again will simply return a new state object, and no state loss\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '// will occur, at the cost of creating more objects.\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'hashState = new MurmurHash3();\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '```\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'Both methods can be mixed however you like if you have different use cases.\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '---\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '### MurmurHash3.prototype.hash (string)\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'Incrementally add _string_ to the hash. This can be called as many times as you want for the hash state object, including after a call to `result()`. Returns `this` so calls can be chained.\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '---\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '### MurmurHash3.prototype.result ()\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'Get the result of the hash as a 32-bit positive integer. This performs the tail and finalizer portions of the algorithm, but does not store the result in the state object. This means that it is perfectly safe to get results and then continue adding strings via `hash`.\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '```javascript\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '// Do the whole string at once\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       "MurmurHash3('this is a test string').result();\n" +
19473 silly install resolved       '// 0x70529328\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '// Do part of the string, get a result, then the other part\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       "var m = MurmurHash3('this is a');\n" +
19473 silly install resolved       'm.result();\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '// 0xbfc4f834\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       "m.hash(' test string').result();\n" +
19473 silly install resolved       '// 0x70529328 (same as above)\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '```\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '---\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '### MurmurHash3.prototype.reset ([seed])\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       'Reset the state object for reuse, optionally using the given _seed_ (defaults to 0 like the constructor). Returns `this` so calls can be chained.\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '\n' +
19473 silly install resolved       '---\n' +
